# Cursor Rules

Load `AGENTS.md` first.

Then load:

- `_system/PROJECT_PROFILE.md`
- `_system/CONTEXT_INDEX.md`
- `_system/LOAD_ORDER.md`
- `_system/WORKING_FILES_GUIDE.md`
- `_system/MASTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`
- `_system/PROJECT_RULES.md`
- `_system/EXECUTION_PROTOCOL.md`
- `_system/MULTI_AGENT_COORDINATION.md`
- `_system/AGENT_DISCOVERY_MATRIX.md`
- `_system/VALIDATION_GATES.md`
- `WHERE_LEFT_OFF.md`
- `TODO.md`
- `FIXME.md`
- `PLAN.md`
- `TEST_STRATEGY.md`

## Defaults

- Minimal diffs, no unrelated refactors.
- Runtime code must not depend on `_system/`.
- Run validation after material changes.
- Keep `.cursor/` rules, commands, and skills aligned with `AGENTS.md`.
- Be aware that `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `CODEX.md`, `WINDSURF.md`, and `.github/copilot-instructions.md` may be used by other tools.
- Load `DESIGN_NOTES.md`, `ARCHITECTURE_NOTES.md`, `RESEARCH_NOTES.md`, `RISK_REGISTER.md`, and `RELEASE_NOTES.md` when the task touches those domains.
